ex S. Vitale analyzes this drive to restore moral order which resulted in an overhaul of the way New York views such social problems as prostitution, graffiti, homelessness, and panhandling. Through several fascinating case studies of New York neighborhoods and an in-depth look at the dynamics of the NYPD and of the city's administration itself, Vitale explains why Republicans have won the last four New York mayoral elections and what the long-term impact Giuliani's zero tolerance method has been on a city historically known for its liberalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aQuality of lifexPolitical aspectszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aQuality of lifezNew York (State)zNew YorkxSociological aspects. 0aQuality of lifezNew York (State)zNew York. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aGiulianis.  aRepublicans.  aThrough.  aVitale.  aYork.  aadministration.  abeen.  acase.  acity.  acitys.  aelections.  aexplains.  afascinating.  afour.  ahave.  ahistorically.  aimpact.  aitself.  aknown.  alast.  aliberalism.  along-term.  amayoral.  amethod.  aseveral.  astudies.  atolerance.  awhat.  azero.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081478817240uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814788417.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814788417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814788417/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK